---
globs: src/http/**, src/controllers/**, src/middleware/**
alwaysApply: false
---

VAIFORM — API ENVELOPE / MIDDLEWARE / CONTROLLER RULES

Applies to:
- src/http/**
- src/controllers/**
- src/middleware/**

Rules:
- All default-reachable JSON API responses must use the canonical envelope:
  - success: { success: true, data, requestId }
  - failure: { success: false, error, detail, fields?, requestId }
- Prefer src/http/respond.js helpers for JSON responses.
- Never reintroduce:
  - ok/reason
  - code/message
  - issues/details
- Keep 5xx detail sanitized; do not leak raw provider/internal exceptions.
- Preserve requestId propagation.
- Use canonical middleware/modules only:
  - requireAuth.js
  - planGuards.js
  - validate.middleware.js + src/schemas/*.schema.js
  - idempotency.firestore.js
- Do not introduce duplicate auth/validation/idempotency/policy helpers.
- Preserve standard middleware order where applicable:
  reqId -> requestContext -> cors -> requireAuth -> plan guards -> idempotency -> validate -> controller
